This paper proposes a novel approach for training deep neural networks by dividing the process into two phases and using Bayesian sampling and stochastic optimization. The paper focuses on optimizing non-convex and high-dimensional objective functions, which is a common problem in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
